Package: shinycorpframe
Title: Corporate-Framed Chart Capture for Shiny
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Simon", "Niederberger", email = "s.niederberger@hotmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Captures Plotly charts in Shiny apps and wraps them with a
    corporate design frame (header with title/subtitle, footer with
    footnotes/sources). Uses shinycapture for browser capture and calls
    a Python/matplotlib postprocessor via subprocess.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/saemeon/dash-interact
Imports:
    shiny (>= 1.7.0),
    shinycapture,
    jsonlite
Suggests:
    plotly,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.0
Config/testthat/edition: 3
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.10), matplotlib
